from your nose and say that again.

248
00:22:45,490 --> 00:22:49,610
Dr. Montague is here.
Thank you. Send him in.

249
00:22:55,450 --> 00:22:58,360
Thank you for coming.
I'm sorry I'm late.

250
00:22:58,450 --> 00:23:01,250
It took longer than anticipated
for my rounds this morning.

251
00:23:01,330 --> 00:23:03,520
Please have a seat.
Thanks.

252
00:23:06,410 --> 00:23:10,480
I'm a little disturbed.
Yes, Dr. Thorndyke?

253
00:23:10,570 --> 00:23:13,560
I've studied some of these case histories
and once in a while...

254
00:23:13,690 --> 00:23:17,760
...I come across a patient who behaves
in a rational and normal manner.

255
00:23:18,170 --> 00:23:20,640
Zachary Cartwright IIl, for instance.

256
00:23:20,850 --> 00:23:24,810
It seems his family is paying
$12,000 a month to the Institute.

257
00:23:25,290 --> 00:23:28,560
According to this file
he should have been released months ago.

258
00:23:28,650 --> 00:23:29,840
Well...

259
00:23:30,130 --> 00:23:33,520
These case histories are really so sketchy.

260
00:23:33,610 --> 00:23:36,960
They hardly draw a true picture
of the patient's psychosis.

261
00:23:37,130 --> 00:23:38,800
Cartwright is a perfect example.

262
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:41,970
One moment he can be
perfectly rational and lucid...

263
00:23:42,130 --> 00:23:45,170
...the next he's a living loony tune.

264
00:23:46,770 --> 00:23:50,520
Do you mind if we examine him together?
He is just outside my door.

265
00:23:50,970 --> 00:23:55,170
Mind? Why should I mind?
After all, you're in charge here.

266
00:23:55,530 --> 00:23:57,840
You can examine anyone you want.

267
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:02,200
Please send Mr. Cartwright in. Thank you.

268
00:24:05,770 --> 00:24:09,520
Mr. Cartwright, have a seat.
You know Dr. Montague, don't you?

269
00:24:10,050 --> 00:24:12,770
- Hello, Dr. Montague.
- Hello, Zack.

270
00:24:19,930 --> 00:24:23,000
Tell me, do you know
why you're here at the Institute?

271
00:24:23,250 --> 00:24:27,880
Yes, I was brought in two years ago.
I was suffering from nervous exhaustion.

272
00:24:28,250 --> 00:24:32,560
I used to get sharp pains in my neck
and dreamt about werewolves.

273
00:24:34,810 --> 00:24:36,760
- Werewolves?
- Werewolves.

274
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:43,360
And in the two years you've been here,
do you feel you've made any progress?

275
00:24:44,010 --> 00:24:46,280
I never get those pains anymore...

276
00:24:46,530 --> 00:24:50,240
...and it's been 6 months
since I had a dream about a werewolf.

277
00:24:50,330 --> 00:24:53,530
6 months since you had
your last dream about a werewolf.

278
00:24:55,170 --> 00:24:59,210
Tell me frankly. If you were
returned to the community today...

279
00:24:59,450 --> 00:25:03,680
...could you function in a happy,
healthy, normal and productive manner?

280
00:25:03,890 --> 00:25:05,920
I think so. I feel pretty good.

281
00:25:07,570 --> 00:25:10,290
- What's the matter?
- That pain just came back.

282
00:25:10,370 --> 00:25:13,760
See how unpredictable he is?
Help him to the couch.

283
00:25:13,850 --> 00:25:18,000
Sit right here. Put your head back.
Breathe deeply. Try to relax.

284
00:25:18,370 --> 00:25:20,040
Easy.
I'll try.

285
00:25:20,130 --> 00:25:23,090
This pain that you haven't experienced
in such a long time...

286
00:25:23,170 --> 00:25:25,560
...has suddenly reappeared for no reason?

287
00:25:25,650 --> 00:25:29,800
- I don't know what it is.
- This is such a strange experience.

288
00:25:30,010 --> 00:25:32,360
- The pain is going away.
- Good. Breathe deeply.

289
00:25:32,490 --> 00:25:33,480
I feel perfectly fine.

290
00:25:34,930 --> 00:25:36,120
What is it?

291
00:25:36,770 --> 00:25:40,120
- Cartwright, is it that same pain?
- Yes!

292
00:25:40,770 --> 00:25:42,650
- Let me examine you.
- No!

293
00:25:43,530 --> 00:25:45,440
I just want to help you!

294
00:25:47,010 --> 00:25:49,600
- I don't understand.
- I don't understand it, either.

295
00:25:49,690 --> 00:25:51,520
Relax, take it easy.

296
00:25:56,330 --> 00:25:58,970
Take it easy!
Go away!

297
00:25:59,090 --> 00:26:02,920
- Montague, what are we going to do?
- I don't know! Take it easy, Zack.

298
00:26:12,050 --> 00:26:13,000
Cartwright!

299
00:26:13,090 --> 00:26:14,810
His feet.
Got him.

300
00:26:17,770 --> 00:26:20,970
Take him back to his room.
Give him a sedative.

301
00:26:22,890 --> 00:26:24,160
Make it a big one.

302
00:26:26,370 --> 00:26:29,200
Sad. I've never seen anything
quite like that.

303
00:26:31,130 --> 00:26:33,320
- And he was doing so well.
- I know.

304
00:26:33,450 --> 00:26:37,000
- lt is sad, tears your heart apart.
- Yes.

305
00:26:37,530 --> 00:26:39,840
- There's that flashing again.
- Flashing?

306
00:26:39,970 --> 00:26:44,360
It started this morning and here it is again.
It seems to be coming from somewhere...

307
00:26:44,490 --> 00:26:47,720
- ...up there.
- Yes, the North Wing.

308
00:26:48,210 --> 00:26:50,200
Room 35, I'd say.

309
00:26:52,370 --> 00:26:54,640
It stopped. Who's in that room?

310
00:26:54,930 --> 00:26:58,050
A patient named Brisbane.
Brisbane.

311
00:26:58,970 --> 00:27:03,010
- Arthur Brisbane? The industrialist?
- Yes, I think that's the one.

312
00:27:03,890 --> 00:27:06,640
- How long has he been here?
- About 18 months.

313
00:27:06,730 --> 00:27:10,000
18 months?
I didn't come across his name in the files.

314
00:27:10,530 --> 00:27:12,360
It must be an oversight.

315
00:27:13,770 --> 00:27:15,090
I'd like to meet him.

316
00:27:15,170 --> 00:27:17,970
But he's hopeless.
You don't want to meet him.

317
00:27:18,250 --> 00:27:20,680
I'd like to meet him right after lunch.

318
00:27:22,530 --> 00:27:24,600
All right. As you wish.

319
00:27:25,890 --> 00:27:28,360
- I'll arrange it for you.
- Thank you.

320
00:27:30,490 --> 00:27:33,130
Nurse Diesel? Dr. Montague here.

321
00:27:33,410 --> 00:27:37,320
Dr. Thorndyke would like to meet
Arthur Brisbane right after lunch.

322
00:27:38,330 --> 00:27:39,440
Good.

323
00:27:39,850 --> 00:27:42,840
Ou-yay ow-knay at-whay o-tay o-day.

324
00:27:43,850 --> 00:27:45,170
Et it-gay?

325
00:27:47,250 --> 00:27:49,600
Everything will be taken care of.

326
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:51,960
There it goes again.

327
00:28:04,730 --> 00:28:05,960
Falling.

328
00:28:06,290 --> 00:28:08,240
Mamma! Falling!

329
00:28:08,330 --> 00:28:12,480
Fight it, Thorndyke. Fight it.
You must fight it, do you hear me?

330
00:28:12,570 --> 00:28:14,130
Fight your fears.

331
00:28:14,250 --> 00:28:18,720
The only way to overcome High Anxiety
is to fight it.

332
00:28:19,450 --> 00:28:20,770
- Fight!
- Fight!

333
00:28:21,130 --> 00:28:23,690
Fight it.
Ja, fight it!

334
00:28:23,970 --> 00:28:25,120
- Fight.
- Good.

335
00:28:25,250 --> 00:28:27,480
Good. Fight it.

336
00:28:27,770 --> 00:28:31,810
Good, fight it.
Ja, good, that's the way to fight it!

337
00:28:31,970 --> 00:28:33,880
Fight it, ja. Good.

338
00:28:38,970 --> 00:28:43,920
That's all right.
Get out that hostility. Good.

339
00:28:44,170 --> 00:28:45,440
Fight.

340
00:28:49,450 --> 00:28:52,880
You want to fight? All right.
Fight if you want. Fight.

341
00:28:52,970 --> 00:28:57,170
I'll give you a fight you don't forget.
Come on, show me your stuff.

342
00:28:57,250 --> 00:28:59,760
Show me your good stuff.
All right, I'll give you...

343
00:29:04,170 --> 00:29:07,400
Come on, get up, you little punk!
Stand up and fight! Come on...

344
00:29:10,850 --> 00:29:14,240
Professor! What are
you doing? This is unseemly behavior.

345
00:29:14,410 --> 00:29:16,440
What are you doing? Stop!

346
00:29:26,250 --> 00:29:30,480
Come on, boys. We came
to see a fight, not a dance. Let's go.

347
00:29:36,210 --> 00:29:38,600
Professor, what happened here?

348
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:43,640
I put him under hypnosis.
He will be out very soon.

349
00:29:43,770 --> 00:29:47,600
You see, we have been running
a series of analytic sessions...

350
00:29:47,810 --> 00:29:50,850
...to try to help him overcome
the very serious illness...

351
00:29:50,930 --> 00:29:53,650
...known as High Anxiety.

352
00:29:54,570 --> 00:29:56,210
- High Anxiety?
- Ja.

353
00:29:58,890 --> 00:30:01,160
Do you mean to say
that Dr. Richard Thorndyke...

354
00:30:01,250 --> 00:30:04,050
...one of the world's
greatest psychiatric authorities...

355
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:06,080
...is suffering from High Anxiety?

356
00:30:06,170 --> 00:30:09,880
Ja, but you would not breathe
a word of this to anyone, would you?

357
00:30:10,130 --> 00:30:13,920
Professor, may I remind you
that I am also a professional?

358
00:30:14,050 --> 00:30:17,480
I am shocked that you would think
I'd say a word about this.

359
00:30:23,810 --> 00:30:28,010
Hey, everybody,
guess who has High Anxiety?

360
00:30:33,970 --> 00:30:36,160
Richard?
Falling, Mamma.

361
00:30:36,250 --> 00:30:37,680
Falling. Mamma. Falling.

362
00:30:37,770 --> 00:30:39,960
Richard, I'm going to bring you out.

363
00:30:40,090 --> 00:30:42,560
I'm going to bring you out. I bring you out!

364
00:30:42,650 --> 00:30:46,640
- Richard, my boy, Richard!
- Professor!

365
00:30:46,730 --> 00:30:49,880
You'll never believe what I just
went through. It was horrible!

366
00:30:49,970 --> 00:30:54,960
I would believe. But there will be
no more sessions for a while.

367
00:30:55,810 --> 00:30:59,400
- So, go get yourself a little rest, my boy.
- Thank you.

368
00:30:59,890 --> 00:31:02,530
- Thank you, Professor.
- Ja, auf Wiedersehen.

369
00:31:09,090 --> 00:31:10,650
Let us see, here.

370
00:31:12,290 --> 00:31:15,680
"Mamma, I am falling."

371
00:31:32,370 --> 00:31:34,930
Norton, this is our new chief,
Dr. Thorndyke.

372
00:31:35,170 --> 00:31:37,970
He'd like to see Mr. Brisbane.
Certainly.

373
00:31:45,090 --> 00:31:48,920
- lt's a pleasure to meet you, Dr. Thorndyke.
- Pleasure to meet you, Norton.

374
00:31:49,890 --> 00:31:53,520
Forgive me for prying.
What happened to your mustache?

375
00:31:55,170 --> 00:31:58,400
As you know, we get some very violent
patients in this wing.

376
00:31:58,610 --> 00:32:00,920
Last week, I guess I wasn't on my toes...

377
00:32:01,130 --> 00:32:05,040
...and one of them reached out
and ripped off half of my mustache.

378
00:32:05,650 --> 00:32:09,800
- That must have been awful.
- You'll never know the pain.

379
00:32:10,770 --> 00:32:13,650
It can get quite dicey up here at times.

380
00:32:14,210 --> 00:32:16,400
- Well, shall we go?
- Follow me.

381
00:32:18,090 --> 00:32:20,320
Hey, Norton! You missing something?

382
00:32:45,130 --> 00:32:47,440
That's Arthur Brisbane? The industrialist?

383
00:32:53,930 --> 00:32:58,400
No. Down, Brisbane, down. Bad Brisbane.

384
00:32:58,890 --> 00:33:01,320
Sit up. All right.

385
00:33:02,770 --> 00:33:05,440
Don't worry, he won't bite.
Just let him smell you.

386
00:33:05,530 --> 00:33:08,800
- He thinks he's a cocker spaniel.
- Cocker spaniel?

387
00:33:15,690 --> 00:33:17,040
Very good.

388
00:33:18,090 --> 00:33:19,920
I've never seen anything like...

389
00:33:20,010 --> 00:33:21,360
Down! Sit!

390
00:33:23,050 --> 00:33:24,370
Stay!

391
00:33:27,250 --> 00:33:31,040
Amazing! The most complex
psychic phenomenon I've ever witnessed.

392
00:33:31,130 --> 00:33:35,040
I once read a paper when I was in college
about this, I think it was Otto Rank.

393
00:33:35,130 --> 00:33:38,920
It might have been Kraft-Ebbing.
About a woman in Vienna...

394
00:33:39,010 --> 00:33:42,080
...who thought that she was an animal
of some kind, an antelope...

395
00:33:42,170 --> 00:33:45,520
What the hell are you...
No! Stop that!

396
00:33:45,610 --> 00:33:48,600
We don't do that with strangers. Bad dog!

397
00:33:50,250 --> 00:33:52,080
Get his leash, Norton.

398
00:33:58,690 --> 00:34:00,090
Extraordinary!

399
00:34:00,170 --> 00:34:04,480
How could a creature have the wherewithal
to try to contact me by flashing a mirror?

400
00:34:04,610 --> 00:34:07,170
Well, cockers are very bright, you know.

401
00:34:08,610 --> 00:34:10,840
That's true. That's very true.

402
00:34:18,730 --> 00:34:20,760
Please understand, I can't go on.

403
00:34:20,850 --> 00:34:24,560
I swear to God, I won't say a word,
but I can't take it any longer.

404
00:34:24,650 --> 00:34:28,440
You're just as much a part of this
as the rest of us.

405
00:34:28,690 --> 00:34:33,130
No one is quitting. Do you hear me?

406
00:34:33,570 --> 00:34:36,130
- No one.
- But I can't sleep at night!

407
00:34:36,450 --> 00:34:39,840
What we're doing is wrong.
Don't you understand, it's wrong!

408
00:34:40,210 --> 00:34:44,570
I've got to get out of here. I'm trapped!
I feel like I'm caught in a web.

409
00:34:45,570 --> 00:34:48,210
Quiet, you fool! The window is open!

410
00:34:58,530 --> 00:34:59,800
All right.

411
00:35:01,370 --> 00:35:02,690
Perhaps...

412
00:35:03,730 --> 00:35:06,770
...l've been too harsh.

413
00:35:07,930 --> 00:35:11,520
You are free to leave the Institute
this evening.

414
00:35:12,810 --> 00:35:15,320
Thank you, Nurse Diesel.

415
00:35:15,610 --> 00:35:18,810
And I promise I won't say anything
to anybody. Thank you.

416
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:21,360
I know you won't.

417
00:35:25,730 --> 00:35:29,400
I know you won't.

418
00:37:53,730 --> 00:37:55,050
Busted eardrums?

419
00:37:55,170 --> 00:37:58,320
That's a very strange symptom
for a cerebral hemorrhage.

420
00:37:58,450 --> 00:38:02,570
According to the coroner's report,
he did suffer from a cerebral hemorrhage.

421
00:38:02,730 --> 00:38:05,120
I can't go to San Francisco now.

422
00:38:05,210 --> 00:38:08,120
Dr. Thorndyke,
there's nothing you can do.

423
00:38:08,290 --> 00:38:12,360
If we receive any additional information
about Wentworth, we'll call you.

424
00:38:12,650 --> 00:38:16,040
It's important that you attend
the psychiatric convention. Remember...

425
00:38:16,130 --> 00:38:19,250
...you are representing the Institute.

426
00:38:19,450 --> 00:38:23,290
Yes, enjoy yourself, for God's sake.
Get your mind off the Wentworth murder.

427
00:38:24,410 --> 00:38:27,080
Accident. Have a good time.

428
00:38:27,930 --> 00:38:30,970
I did work long and hard on that speech.

429
00:38:33,210 --> 00:38:35,410
I'm going. You've convinced me. Brophy!

430
00:38:35,530 --> 00:38:38,250
I'm looking for my camera,
I want to get one last shot.

431
00:38:39,130 --> 00:38:40,800
Please, Brophy, not now.

432
00:38:41,690 --> 00:38:42,970
Hold it!

433
00:38:44,770 --> 00:38:47,600
- Okay, let's hit the road.
- Well, see you in three days.

434
00:38:47,690 --> 00:38:50,160
Bye-bye.
Bye-bye.

435
00:38:50,770 --> 00:38:52,920
Enjoy yourself.
'Bye.

436
00:38:55,850 --> 00:38:58,650
I think you punctured something
with that last shot.

437
00:38:58,770 --> 00:39:01,000
You do everything too hard. Too hard.

438
00:39:01,650 --> 00:39:03,400
Come to my room right after dinner.

439
00:39:03,490 --> 00:39:06,290
Not tonight. I'm too tired.
I'm going to turn in early.

440
00:39:06,410 --> 00:39:09,370
- I'll let you wear my underwear.
- I'll be there.

441
00:39:46,450 --> 00:39:48,570
Thorndyke and Brophy.
Yes, sir.

442
00:39:49,290 --> 00:39:50,280
Thank you.

443
00:39:55,810 --> 00:39:58,610
Dr. Richard H. Thorndyke?
Yes.

444
00:39:58,770 --> 00:40:00,970
Sir, very good. Here we go, you're all set.

445
00:40:01,090 --> 00:40:02,840
Wow. Talk about modern.

446
00:40:02,970 --> 00:40:05,800
You and Mr. Brophy are in 1702 and 1703.

447
00:40:07,050 --> 00:40:10,930
Excuse me. I thought I'd specifically
requested a room on a lower floor.

448
00:40:11,010 --> 00:40:15,240
- Nothing higher than three.
- We had 201 all set for you.

449
00:40:15,610 --> 00:40:19,890
But a Mr. MacGuffin called
and told us to change it to the 17th floor.

450
00:40:20,930 --> 00:40:24,210
I'm sorry, we can't do a thing
about it today. We're all booked up.

451
00:40:24,370 --> 00:40:26,890
Come on, Doc.
It's only for a couple of nights.

452
00:40:28,370 --> 00:40:31,040
I guess it'll be all right. It's just...

453
00:40:32,010 --> 00:40:35,770
...I really don't like high places.

454
00:40:38,810 --> 00:40:42,410
Dennis, will you take Dr. Thorndyke
to his room, please?

455
00:40:42,890 --> 00:40:44,290
Anything I can get you?

456
00:40:44,370 --> 00:40:45,880
Yes. I'd like a newspaper.

457
00:40:45,970 --> 00:40:48,570
I'll get you one and meet you
at the elevators.

458
00:40:48,650 --> 00:40:52,090
- Please don't forget. It's rather important.
- All right, already.

459
00:40:54,570 --> 00:40:57,640
I want to see if there's any mention
of Wentworth's death.

460
00:40:57,730 --> 00:40:59,690
Doc, there are the elevators.

461
00:41:04,610 --> 00:41:08,210
- Come on, Doc.
- I'm coming.

462
00:41:13,610 --> 00:41:16,050
Here we go. Straight to the top.

463
00:41:24,410 --> 00:41:25,840
Quite a view, isn't it?

464
00:41:34,330 --> 00:41:38,450
Here we are. Top floor. Top of the hotel.
You can't get any higher.

465
00:41:38,530 --> 00:41:41,330
- We're pretty high.
- We know it. We know we're high.

466
00:41:41,450 --> 00:41:43,280
That we know. That part we know.

467
00:41:51,090 --> 00:41:54,240
Excuse me. This way.

468
00:41:59,490 --> 00:42:01,800
This way, please. Right around the corner.

469
00:42:01,930 --> 00:42:06,640
Hey, Doc, look at this.
What a view. This is spectacular.

470
00:42:08,530 --> 00:42:13,050
I can see it from here.
It's very nice. Very nice indeed.

471
00:42:29,890 --> 00:42:32,120
Are you all right, Doc?

472
00:42:33,330 --> 00:42:35,290
I'm all right, Brophy.

473
00:42:36,730 --> 00:42:40,520
I'm sorry, sir.
I didn't know anyone was there.

474
00:42:44,210 --> 00:42:46,960
You fellas want to see your rooms or not?

475
00:42:49,170 --> 00:42:51,080
Let's get out of here.

476
00:42:58,130 --> 00:43:01,360
If you would have gone over
you'd be smashed like corned beef hash.

477
00:43:01,450 --> 00:43:04,170
Your brains would have splattered
all over the lobby...

478
00:43:04,250 --> 00:43:06,000
Brophy, please.

479
00:43:08,410 --> 00:43:12,120
Right here is 1702. You're in 1703.

480
00:43:12,410 --> 00:43:15,210
Here's your key.
I'll bring your bag in a minute.

481
00:43:15,490 --> 00:43:17,080
See you later. Thank you.

482
00:43:26,570 --> 00:43:29,130
- Here you go. Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

