01:23:43,300 --> 01:23:46,740
Hold on! Pull yourself up! You can do it!

979
01:23:48,140 --> 01:23:49,730
I can't hang on!

980
01:23:53,180 --> 01:23:55,700
That's it! Richard, listen to me!

981
01:23:55,980 --> 01:23:59,890
I have researched your case.
I know what's giving you the High Anxiety.

982
01:23:59,980 --> 01:24:01,890
I have found the answer.

983
01:24:01,980 --> 01:24:04,210
Go back in your mind. Go back.

984
01:24:04,300 --> 01:24:05,970
You are a little baby.

985
01:24:06,060 --> 01:24:09,420
Your mother and father are fighting.
They're always fighting.

986
01:24:09,500 --> 01:24:11,570
They're fighting about you.

987
01:24:19,420 --> 01:24:22,460
I hate this kid! He's making us prisoners!

988
01:24:22,540 --> 01:24:24,740
We're trapped in this house!
We can never go out!

989
01:24:24,820 --> 01:24:28,700
What do you want me to do?
Get rid of him? Is that what you want?

990
01:24:28,780 --> 01:24:30,100
Shut him up!

991
01:24:30,180 --> 01:24:32,410
Shut him up! I can't take it!

992
01:24:32,540 --> 01:24:33,970
He's falling!

993
01:24:37,780 --> 01:24:39,530
I understand now.

994
01:24:41,180 --> 01:24:44,890
It's not height I'm afraid of. It's parents!

995
01:24:45,300 --> 01:24:46,580
Ja.

996
01:24:47,980 --> 01:24:51,860
Now climb, you son-of-a-bitch. Climb!

997
01:24:58,540 --> 01:25:01,420
Come on, Doc. You can do it.

998
01:25:06,020 --> 01:25:07,850
He's almost at the top.

999
01:25:10,540 --> 01:25:11,580
Hurry, Richard.

1000
01:25:19,540 --> 01:25:20,970
Come on, Doc.

1001
01:25:38,340 --> 01:25:39,690
Norton.

1002
01:25:44,500 --> 01:25:46,220
Oh, my God.

1003
01:25:51,540 --> 01:25:54,930
- Mr. Brisbane, are you all right?
- Yes, I'm all right.

1004
01:25:56,940 --> 01:25:58,740
Get down the stairs.

1005
01:25:58,820 --> 01:26:00,890
Thank you. You saved my life.

1006
01:26:00,980 --> 01:26:02,330
Thank God it's over.

1007
01:26:25,620 --> 01:26:27,980
Fins. I give up.

1008
01:26:28,060 --> 01:26:31,130
I never really liked her. She never bathed.

1009
01:26:31,300 --> 01:26:34,660
But I like you, I'll be on your side.
I'll do anything you say.

1010
01:26:34,740 --> 01:26:38,450
I'm good at that. If I don't behave
you can beat the living crap out of me.

1011
01:26:38,540 --> 01:26:40,020
I wouldn't mind.

1012
01:26:41,340 --> 01:26:43,620
Are you all right? We saw a figure fall.

1013
01:26:43,700 --> 01:26:46,060
That was Nurse Diesel,
she went out this window.

1014
01:26:46,140 --> 01:26:48,610
Daddy, I love you.
My baby.

1015
01:26:48,700 --> 01:26:50,340
My boss.

1016
01:26:50,540 --> 01:26:52,930
Brophy.
My Richard.

1017
01:26:53,580 --> 01:26:55,330
Professor.

1018
01:26:55,820 --> 01:26:57,410
- You saved my life.
- Ja.

1019
01:26:57,780 --> 01:26:59,980
You saved my life. Who are you?

1020
01:27:00,060 --> 01:27:01,260
Dad.

1021
01:27:02,500 --> 01:27:04,860
This is the man I'm going to marry.

1022
01:27:04,980 --> 01:27:08,180
Jeepers, Vicky.
Isn't he a dreamboat?

1023
01:27:11,060 --> 01:27:12,380
Goodbye, Dad.

1024
01:27:22,180 --> 01:27:24,460
I absolutely love my new name.

1025
01:27:24,820 --> 01:27:27,890
Mrs. Victoria Harpo Thorndyke.

1026
01:27:28,620 --> 01:27:32,220
Mrs. Dr. Victoria Harpo Thorndyke.

1027
01:27:32,460 --> 01:27:34,020
Yes. Doctor?

1028
01:27:34,740 --> 01:27:36,570
I'm having this problem.

1029
01:27:36,940 --> 01:27:38,500
Problem? Well...

1030
01:27:38,700 --> 01:27:41,260
...maybe we should examine the situation.

1031
01:27:41,340 --> 01:27:43,810
Nice shot.
Pull the camera back slowly.

1032
01:27:43,900 --> 01:27:46,940
We're going too fast,
we're going to hit the wall.

1033
01:27:50,060 --> 01:27:51,570
Now what do we do?

1034
01:27:51,660 --> 01:27:55,180
Never mind. Keep pulling back.
Maybe nobody will notice.

